╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
║  HELIX TRAINER — Exercise 3.2: Yank and Paste                   ║
║  Category: Changes               Difficulty: ★☆☆ Fundamental    ║
╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

COMMANDS TO LEARN
─────────────────
  y     Yank (copy) selection to register
  p     Paste after selection
  P     Paste before selection
  R     Replace selection with yanked text

INSTRUCTIONS
────────────
  The first line contains a template. Copy it and use it to
  replace the placeholder text on each subsequent line.

  Strategy:
  1. On line 1, press x to select the line, then y to yank
  2. Move to line 2, press x to select it
  3. Press R to replace with the yanked text
  4. Repeat for lines 3 and 4

────────────────────────── PRACTICE ──────────────────────────────

Hello, World!
REPLACE_ME_1
REPLACE_ME_2
REPLACE_ME_3

────────────────────────── EXPECTED ──────────────────────────────

Hello, World!
Hello, World!
Hello, World!
Hello, World!

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HINTS (read only if stuck):
  Hint 1: Select the first line with x, yank with y.
  Hint 2: Move down to REPLACE_ME_1, select with x.
  Hint 3: Press R to replace the selection with "Hello, World!"
  Hint 4: R replaces the current selection with register contents.
          This is different from p (paste after) and P (paste before).
